"Şenyiǧit U., Akbolat D.","The effect of different irrigation methods on soil carbon dioxide emission [Farkli{dotless} sulama yöntemlerinin topraktan karbondioksit (CO2) çi{dotless}ki{dotless}şi{dotless} üzerine etkisi]",2010,"Ekoloji",,"77",,"59","64",,,10.5053/ekoloji.2010.779,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-78649937666&partnerID=40&md5=9fe13326453ed11140bce103a8e66bc8","Süleyman Demirel Üniversitesi, Ziraat Fakültesi, Tarimsal Yapilar ve Sulama Bölümü, 32260 Çünür, Isparta, Turkey; Süleyman Demirel Üniversitesi, Ziraat Fakültesi, Tarim Makineleri Bölümü, 32260 Çünür, Isparta, Turkey","Şenyiǧit, U., Süleyman Demirel Üniversitesi, Ziraat Fakültesi, Tarimsal Yapilar ve Sulama Bölümü, 32260 Çünür, Isparta, Turkey; Akbolat, D., Süleyman Demirel Üniversitesi, Ziraat Fakültesi, Tarim Makineleri Bölümü, 32260 Çünür, Isparta, Turkey","Global warming and greenhouse gas emission are one of the important researches in recent years. There are a wide range of greenhouse gas resources and one of them is agricultural activities. During agricultural activities CO2 emission from soil occurs. Water requirement in plant production is met by using various irrigation methods. The most widely used methods are drip irrigation, sprinkler irrigation and surface irrigation. Drip irrigation in recent years has been preferred due to its less water use. This study was carried out to determine soil CO2 emission in apple orchard of Jersey Mac apple cultivars grafted on M9 which was irrigated by drip irrigation, sprinkler irrigation and surface irrigation methods. In the study, soil CO2 flux was measured after irrigation. CO2 flux of drip, sprinkler and surface irrigation was 0.065, 0.071 and 0.084 g.CO2.m-2.h-1, respectively. Evaporation from the soil was 8.06, 8.85 and 8.95 g.H2O.m-2.h-1 for drip, sprinkler and surface irrigation, respectively. Even though there were no significant differences among irrigation methods in terms of CO2 flux and evaporation value (P&gt;0.05), these results indicated that CO2 emission and evaporation values in drip irrigation method tended to decrease.","Drip irrigation; Flux; Greenhouse gasses; Irrigation methods; Soil CO2","agricultural practice; carbon dioxide; carbon flux; cultivar; drip irrigation; evaporation; fruit; global warming; greenhouse gas; orchard; soil emission; Malus x domestica",,,,,,"Akbolat, D., Evrendilek, F., Coskan, A., Ekinci, K., Quantifying soil respiration in response to short-term tillage practices: A case study in southern Turkey. Acta Agriculturae Scandinavica (2009) Section B - Plant Soil Science, 59 (1), pp. 50-56; Akgül, M., Bathayidit, L., Süleyman Demirel Üniversitesi Çiftlik Arazisinin Detayli{dotless} Toprak Etüdü ve Haritalanmasi{dotless}. Süleyman Demirel Üniversitesi (2005) Fen Bilimleri Enstitü Dergisi, 9 (3), pp. 54-63; Blake, G.R., Hartge, K.K., Bulk density (1986) Methods of Soil Analysis, Part 1. Physical and Mineralogical Methods: Agronomy Monograph, 9, pp. 363-382. , In: Klute A, Soil Science Society of America Publications, Madison; Blanke, M.M., Soil respiration in an apple orchard (1996) Environmental and Experimental Biology, 36 (3), pp. 339-348; Calderon, F.J., Jackson, L.E., Rototillage, Disking, and Subsequent irrigation: Effects on Soil Nitrogen Dynamics, Microbial Biomas, and Carbon Dioxide Efflux (2002) Journal of Environmental Quality, 31, pp. 752-758; Ceritli, I., Türkiye'nin toprak sorunu (1997) Ekoloji, 22, pp. 4-8; Einhorn, T., Caspari, H.W., Partial Rootzone Drying and Deficit Irrigation of Gala Apples in A Semi-Arid Climate (2004) Acta Horticulturue (ISHS), 664, pp. 197-204; Gültekin, A.H.H., Örgün, Y., Tari{dotless}m toprag ̌i{dotless}nda bitki besleyici elementlerin rolü (1994) Ekoloji, 13, pp. 27-32; Jabro, J.D., Sainju, U., Stevens, W.B., Evans, R.G., Carbon dioxide flux as affected by tillage and irrigation in soil converted from perennial forages to annual crops (2008) Journal of Environmental Management, 88, pp. 1478-1484; Kanber, R., 